cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PF, cs.PL, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on efficient parallelization of merging two sorted arrays. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents a novel approach to partitioning two input sorted arrays and offers insights into cache-efficient sequential sorting. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper discusses load balancing and minimizing extra work brought about by parallelization. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper presents a synchronization-free merging algorithm. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also relevant as the paper discusses the importance of efficient use of memory.
